<subSubSection id="C36B652A81B7FF1BFF31FB66FAECFA8E" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCE36A181B7FF1BFF31FB66FC23FB22" blockId="152.[136,1451,1202,1373]" box="[189,912,1238,1265]" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B905EAB381B7FF1BFF31FB66FEC6FB22" bold="true" box="[189,373,1238,1264]" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Distribution:—</emphasis>
Northern 
<collectingCountry id="F366763181B7FF1BFE6DFB67FDFDFB23" box="[481,590,1239,1265]" name="Myanmar" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(?) and southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F366763181B7FF1BFCC9FB66FC3FFB22" box="[837,908,1238,1264]" name="China" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36A181B7FF1BFF31FB4AFAECFA8E" blockId="152.[136,1451,1202,1373]" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B905EAB381B7FF1BFF31FB4AFE95FAC6" bold="true" box="[189,294,1274,1300]" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Notes:—</emphasis>
Based on the petal and lip shape the specimen is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D2281B7FF1BFC46FB4BFBE4FAC6" authorityName="X. H. Jin, Schuit. &amp; Raskoti, PhytoKeys" authorityYear="2017" box="[970,1111,1274,1300]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Herminium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tibeticum">
<emphasis id="B905EAB381B7FF1BFC46FB4BFBE4FAC6" box="[970,1111,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">H. tibeticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(B.B. Raskoti, pers. comm.), currently only known from southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F366763181B7FF1BFDEAFAAEFD1EFAEA" box="[614,685,1310,1336]" name="China" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">China</collectingCountry>
. It differs by being a smaller plant with longer sepals and a much shorter lip callus. One flower was here observed to be abnormal, with an extra theca formed in front of a petal.
</paragraph>
